Shift by k is equivalent with the following:
1. reverse whole array
2. reverse first subarray of k elements
3. reverse the remaining subarray

Check out similar question: https://leetcode.com/problems/rotate-array/

```
class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> shiftGrid(int[][] grid, int k) {

        int m = grid.length, n = grid[0].length;
        k = k % (m*n);
        int[] arr = new int[m*n];
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++){
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++){
                arr[i*n+j] = grid[i][j];
            }
        }

        reverseArray(arr, 0, m*n-1);
        reverseArray(arr, 0, k-1);
        reverseArray(arr, k, m*n-1);

        List<List<Integer>> res = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++){
            List<Integer> row = new ArrayList<>();
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++){
                row.add(arr[i*n+j]);
            }
            res.add(row);
        }

        return res;
    }

    private void reverseArray(int[] arr, int start, int end) {
        while (start < end) {
            int temp = arr[start];
            arr[start] = arr[end];
            arr[end] = temp;
            start++;
            end--;
        }
    }
}
```

