If you are familiar with [RotateArray](https://leetcode.com/problems/rotate-array/submissions/) and  [Search a 2D Matrix](https://leetcode.com/problems/search-a-2d-matrix/) this is using concept of both .

just assuming matrix as 1D array using arr[i/lenOfRow][i%lenOfRow] and reverse the array and fill the matrix into arraylist and return 
TC:O(N*M)    SC:O(1)
Comment if needed improvements ;)

```
class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> shiftGrid(int[][] grid, int k) {
        List<List<Integer>> ans= new ArrayList<>();
        int m=grid.length;
        int n=grid[0].length;
        int len=n*m;
            k=k%(m*n);
        reverse(grid,len-k,len-1);
        reverse(grid,0,len-k-1);
        reverse(grid,0,len-1);
        for(int i=0;i<m;i++){
              List<Integer> l= new ArrayList<>();
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                l.add(grid[i][j]);
            }
            ans.add(l);       
        }
        return ans;
    }
    public void reverse(int [][] grid,int i,int j){
        int n=grid[0].length;
        while(i<j){
            int temp=grid[i/n][i%n];
            grid[i/n][i%n]=grid[j/n][j%n];
            grid[j/n][j%n]=temp;
            i++;
            j--;
        }
    }
}
